Description. Holotype : Male (
Figs. 28–30
). Total length 3.3 mm , greatest width 1.3 mm . Body elongate, with sub-parallel sides, moderately convex.

Genitalia:
Parameres slightly shorter than median lobe. Parameres in dorsal view (

Fig. 
29

) very narrowed towards apex, where they are strongly bent inwards; apex truncate. The apical half of parameres features a small ventral toothlike projection directed obliquely inwards. Parameres in lateral view (

Fig. 
30

) wide at base narrowing towards the apex. Median lobe in dorsal view (

Fig. 
29

) extending little beyond the parameres; surface strongly compressed dorsoventrally towards the apex, slightly concave in the apical half. Near the apex, lateral margins of the median lobe have a slight protuberance on both side directed outwards and slightly forwards; basolateral apophyses very stout. Median lobe in lateral view (

Fig. 
30

) with apex slightly bent downwards. Phallobase (
Figs. 29, 30
) asymmetrical.
